description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered Mental Health Nurse, Social Worker, Occupational Therapist?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a really exciting time to join our Home Treatment Services in Somerset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to have been successful in receiving additional investment to our Home Treatment Services and we are now providing a significantly improved service and pathway for people coming into contact with our teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have recently been involved in collaboration with the Local Authority and specialist mental health providers to provide a Step- Up facility in Yeovil which this Home Treatment Team supports . This is providing an effective treatment pathway as an alternative to a hospital admission and support more effective recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a registered and highly motivated mental health professional who is interested in working in the Home Treatment Team (Crisis Service), based in Yeovil.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll deliver high-quality rapid assessments, including assessment of risk, formulations and care plans for people who present in a mental health crisis. Assessments can take place in mental health, acute care and community settings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a rapidly expanding Multi-Disciplinary Team including Psychologists and Psychiatrist. You&#39;ll be a key member of the team, liaising with statutory services and other agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work includes gatekeeping admissions and facilitating discharge and you will be expected to maintain a high standard of electronic patient records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our current shift pattern supports a positive work life balance with 3 x 12.5 hr shifts being worked in a full week, allowing plenty of time away from the workplace to recharge and take care of yourself. Our trust has excellent Wellbeing support for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will involve flexible working across a 24-hour shift rota (days, evenings and night shifts) in a 7 day a week service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carla Moreira&lt;/p&gt;
